WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.470 --> 00:00:03.904
<i>And in time... enough time...</i>

2
00:00:03.972 --> 00:00:05.906
<i>I would forget.</i>

3
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.com ] ==-

4
00:00:20.322 --> 00:00:21.755
Yeah.

5
00:00:23.525 --> 00:00:24.958
All right.

6
00:00:29.397 --> 00:00:31.422
A little fixer-upper
south of Wilshire.

7
00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:33.434
It's nothing. Yeah.

8
00:00:34.903 --> 00:00:36.393
I've got people here.

9
00:00:37.172 --> 00:00:39.231
Yeah. I'll talk to you later.

10
00:00:39.307 --> 00:00:40.239
Sorry.

11
00:00:40.308 --> 00:00:42.538
I'm here for you now.

12
00:00:42.611 --> 00:00:45.341
All right.
two acres on Alta Loma.

13
00:00:45.413 --> 00:00:47.574
- Alta Vista.
- Vista. That's right.

14
00:00:47.649 --> 00:00:48.980
Murphy property.

15
00:00:49.851 --> 00:00:52.581
We've been a little late on
the payments. want to settle up.

16
00:00:53.255 --> 00:00:55.348
I don't think that's possible.

17
00:00:56.391 --> 00:00:57.483
What do you mean?

18
00:00:57.559 --> 00:00:59.686
The mortgage
is two months in default...

19
00:00:59.761 --> 00:01:04.289
and it appears that the property
is in contract to another party.

20
00:01:05.534 --> 00:01:07.092
To another party?

21
00:01:07.168 --> 00:01:08.726
- Who?
- That's privileged information.

22
00:01:08.803 --> 00:01:11.829
How can that be? We called
specifically for an extension.

23
00:01:11.907 --> 00:01:14.637
The extension
expired two days ago.

24
00:01:14.709 --> 00:01:17.701
If you don't make a payment.
the bank can repossess.

25
00:01:17.779 --> 00:01:19.576
Without prior notice?

26
00:01:19.648 --> 00:01:22.014
Can they do that?

27
00:01:22.083 --> 00:01:23.710
They don't have to warn us.

28
00:01:23.785 --> 00:01:26.720
But. in fact. an attempt was made
to call you on the third...

29
00:01:26.788 --> 00:01:29.348
and a registered letter.
return receipt requested...

30
00:01:29.424 --> 00:01:30.857
was attempted on the fourth.

31
00:01:30.926 --> 00:01:32.860
Apparently
there was no one home.

32
00:01:32.928 --> 00:01:34.589
We were out of town.

33
00:01:34.663 --> 00:01:36.722
Well. I am sorry...

34
00:01:36.798 --> 00:01:39.062
but you snooze. you lose.

35
00:01:41.303 --> 00:01:42.736
"You snooze. you lose."

36
00:01:44.739 --> 00:01:46.366
"You snooze. you lose"?

37
00:01:46.441 --> 00:01:48.909
- It's an expression.
- Oh. that's beautiful.

38
00:01:51.046 --> 00:01:52.570
Bullshit!

39
00:01:54.549 --> 00:01:56.210
This is bullshit. man!

40
00:01:56.284 --> 00:01:57.876
Don't deal with these people.

41
00:01:57.953 --> 00:02:00.888
They sold us out.
They'll sell you out too.

42
00:02:46.368 --> 00:02:48.768
Hi. Wanna help me
in the garden?

43
00:02:51.006 --> 00:02:52.735
Okay.

44
00:03:01.549 --> 00:03:04.484
Our tomatoes are looking good.
Don't you think?

45
00:03:07.122 --> 00:03:08.555
David?

46
00:03:11.793 --> 00:03:13.818
What's "Gryphon"?

47
00:03:15.296 --> 00:03:16.729
<i>Gryphon.</i>

48
00:03:18.466 --> 00:03:20.661
Where'd you hear that name?

49
00:03:21.936 --> 00:03:24.029
You have a box of matches.

50
00:03:26.608 --> 00:03:28.838
We said we wouldn't
talk about it.

51
00:03:28.910 --> 00:03:31.470
Yeah. well. now
I want to talk about it.

52
00:03:33.415 --> 00:03:34.848
Don't you?

53
00:03:36.017 --> 00:03:37.450
No.

54
00:03:37.519 --> 00:03:39.146
D.

55
00:03:41.423 --> 00:03:44.915
I thought I could forget about this.
but I can't.

56
00:03:44.993 --> 00:03:46.426
So I think...

57
00:03:47.796 --> 00:03:51.129
maybe if we just talk about it
we can put it behind us.

58
00:03:57.739 --> 00:03:59.331
<i>Gryphors</i> a boat.

59
00:04:00.842 --> 00:04:03.276
He took you to a boat?

60
00:04:03.344 --> 00:04:05.812
- In Nevada?
- We flew to Santa Barbara.

61
00:04:06.614 --> 00:04:09.048
- What kind of boat?
- A big boat.

62
00:04:09.117 --> 00:04:10.550
And then what?

63
00:04:10.618 --> 00:04:12.017
And then nothing.

64
00:04:15.189 --> 00:04:18.158
Where did you get the matches?
Have you been going through my bag?

65
00:04:18.226 --> 00:04:19.386
No.

66
00:04:22.964 --> 00:04:24.898
Why? What's in your bag?

67
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:28.635
I'm not gonna talk about this.
I'm not gonna do it.

68
00:06:06.067 --> 00:06:07.591
What?

69
00:06:09.103 --> 00:06:11.162
Who are you talking to?

70
00:06:12.006 --> 00:06:13.303
My mother.

71
00:06:13.975 --> 00:06:16.671
And what did Mom have to say?

72
00:06:18.746 --> 00:06:20.771
Nothing. She wasrt there.

73
00:06:20.848 --> 00:06:25.114
You said you were talking to her.
How could you if she wasrt there?

74
00:06:25.186 --> 00:06:27.552
Well. I was trying
to talk to her...

75
00:06:27.622 --> 00:06:29.283
but I didn't reach her.

76
00:06:29.357 --> 00:06:31.291
She wasrt in after 10:00?

77
00:06:31.359 --> 00:06:34.419
No. If you don't believe me. would
you like to talk to her yourself?

78
00:06:39.166 --> 00:06:41.361
What is the matter with you?

79
00:06:47.575 --> 00:06:48.872
What is that?

80
00:06:48.943 --> 00:06:50.934
You know what it is.

81
00:06:54.315 --> 00:06:56.510
- Where did you get this?
- In your wallet.

82
00:06:57.718 --> 00:06:59.151
I've never seen it before.

83
00:06:59.220 --> 00:07:02.018
- It was in the secret compartment.
- I don't even use that.

84
00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:04.353
- Have you been seeing him?
- No. I haven't.

85
00:07:04.425 --> 00:07:07.292
- You can't stop thinking about him.
- You won't let me.

86
00:07:08.529 --> 00:07:11.123
- Why were you in my wallet. anyway?
- I don't trust you.

87
00:07:11.198 --> 00:07:14.725
- Well. I don't trust you either.
- Well. then we're even.

88
00:07:23.978 --> 00:07:25.912
<i>I had to do something.</i>

89
00:07:25.980 --> 00:07:28.915
<i>I wanted to make something good</i>
<i>out of all we'd done wrong.</i>

90
00:07:28.983 --> 00:07:31.918
<i>I decided to try</i>
<i>and buy our land back.</i>

91
00:07:34.288 --> 00:07:35.721
Alta Vista.

92
00:07:35.790 --> 00:07:38.816
I need to find out the guy's name.
I wanna make him an offer.

93
00:07:39.994 --> 00:07:42.292
I'm gonna get killed
for this. Diana.

94
00:07:42.363 --> 00:07:46.231
I don't want you to get in trouble.
I really appreciate it.

95
00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:48.666
There it is.
Right there.

96
00:07:48.736 --> 00:07:50.397
- Back up.
- Here we go.

97
00:07:50.471 --> 00:07:52.962
543 Alta Vista.

98
00:07:54.475 --> 00:07:55.567
Oh. my God.

99
00:07:55.643 --> 00:07:58.237
This guy's never gonna sell.

100
00:07:58.312 --> 00:08:00.906
I just saw this guy on TV.

101
00:08:41.155 --> 00:08:43.146
You bastard!
You stole our property!

102
00:08:45.459 --> 00:08:47.393
Gentlemen.
I'd like to introduce a friend...

103
00:08:47.461 --> 00:08:48.655
I'm not your friend.

104
00:08:49.630 --> 00:08:52.428
Diana advised me on a piece
of property in Santa Monica.

105
00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:54.934
You're a liar.
You took it. and I want it back.

106
00:08:55.002 --> 00:08:58.130
Can we have a... Everything's fine.
Everything's under control.

107
00:08:58.205 --> 00:08:59.467
Very well. sir.

108
00:09:01.308 --> 00:09:02.741
Excuse me.

109
00:09:10.484 --> 00:09:12.418
I'm taking it off.

110
00:09:15.656 --> 00:09:16.953
Wait a minute.

111
00:09:17.024 --> 00:09:20.790
- Did you just want to hurt me?
- Nonsense. I think you're wonderful.

112
00:09:20.861 --> 00:09:22.761
- That was our house.
- I got there first.

113
00:09:22.830 --> 00:09:24.957
I want you
to sell it back to me.

114
00:09:25.032 --> 00:09:27.899
- You can't afford it.
- Oh? How's a million dollars?

115
00:09:27.968 --> 00:09:29.731
The price is two.

116
00:09:29.804 --> 00:09:32.204
If I had two.
the price would be four. right?

117
00:09:32.273 --> 00:09:34.207
I saw an opportunity
and I took it.

118
00:09:34.275 --> 00:09:38.234
You had the money and the right
instincts. but you were too late.

119
00:09:38.312 --> 00:09:40.872
- I want you to work for me.
- You go to hell.

120
00:09:40.948 --> 00:09:42.472
Listen. I mean it.

121
00:09:42.550 --> 00:09:44.541
- Never.
- Why not?

122
00:09:45.453 --> 00:09:48.013
- Because I hate you.
- No. you don't.

123
00:09:49.290 --> 00:09:51.850
You wish you hated me.

124
00:10:11.979 --> 00:10:13.742
Hi. D.

125
00:10:17.785 --> 00:10:19.719
You look awful.

126
00:10:21.255 --> 00:10:24.520
- Where you been?
- I'll tell you about it.

127
00:10:24.592 --> 00:10:26.617
Gonna have some wine first.

128
00:10:29.663 --> 00:10:30.755
Do you want some?

129
00:10:55.256 --> 00:10:56.587
So. where you been?

130
00:11:02.162 --> 00:11:06.258
Last night I was up for hours trying
to figure a way out of this mess.

131
00:11:09.302 --> 00:11:10.564
And today?

132
00:11:14.407 --> 00:11:16.238
And today I saw Gage.

133
00:11:24.317 --> 00:11:26.751
Thank you for your trust. David...

134
00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:28.287
and for listening.

135
00:11:28.922 --> 00:11:30.355
Did you fuck him?

136
00:11:30.423 --> 00:11:32.118
- No.
- But you wanted to.

137
00:11:32.192 --> 00:11:34.922
I met him in broad daylight in
front of a bunch of rich assholes.

138
00:11:34.995 --> 00:11:36.087
I don't believe you.

139
00:11:36.162 --> 00:11:39.427
David. he bought our property.
Okay?

140
00:11:39.499 --> 00:11:43.595
That's why I went to see him...
to find some way to get it back.

141
00:11:45.305 --> 00:11:48.274
You have no reason to be jealous.
I hate him.

142
00:11:49.543 --> 00:11:53.570
- Tell me what happened on that boat.
- Don't do this!

143
00:11:53.647 --> 00:11:54.579
Why?

144
00:11:54.648 --> 00:11:56.513
'Cause I want to know.

145
00:11:56.583 --> 00:12:00.178
All right. I'll tell you.
The man was a fucking stallion.

146
00:12:00.253 --> 00:12:03.313
Should I say we did it all night?
Does that do it for you?

147
00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:06.223
- Is that the truth?
- You don't want the fucking truth.

148
00:12:06.293 --> 00:12:08.227
You want me to lie.

149
00:12:08.295 --> 00:12:11.162
So I'll tell you he's awful.
and you won't believe me.

150
00:12:11.231 --> 00:12:13.791
Just tell me the truth. D.

151
00:12:13.867 --> 00:12:15.562
It was sex. David.

152
00:12:15.635 --> 00:12:17.466
Just sex. Not love.

153
00:12:17.537 --> 00:12:19.698
Was it good sex?

154
00:12:19.773 --> 00:12:22.173
- Don't do this.
- Can you just tell me that?

155
00:12:22.242 --> 00:12:25.268
What are you hesitating for?
Just tell me. Was it good?

156
00:12:25.345 --> 00:12:27.279
Was it good? Was it good?

157
00:12:28.148 --> 00:12:29.581
Yes.

158
00:12:40.126 --> 00:12:41.616
David.

159
00:12:47.167 --> 00:12:50.694
Don't tell me it was just sex.
You were attracted to him all along.

160
00:12:50.770 --> 00:12:54.171
That's bullshit.
David. I did it for you.

161
00:12:54.240 --> 00:12:56.174
Don't you tell me
you did it for me.

162
00:12:56.242 --> 00:12:59.234
You did it for yourself.
You were dying to do it.

163
00:12:59.312 --> 00:13:02.873
I would never do this for myself.
It was all for you.

164
00:13:02.949 --> 00:13:04.541
Don't lie to me!

165
00:13:04.618 --> 00:13:06.552
You were attracted to him!

166
00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:10.215
I knew something like this
was gonna happen.

167
00:14:10.283 --> 00:14:13.582
I guess you make a deal
with the devil...

168
00:14:13.653 --> 00:14:15.587
and eventually
you pay the price.

169
00:14:15.655 --> 00:14:17.646
Thanks. Jeremy.

170
00:14:17.724 --> 00:14:21.216
Coming from the man who closed
the deal. that's very comforting.

171
00:14:24.731 --> 00:14:26.722
Green.

172
00:14:26.800 --> 00:14:27.892
Oh. hi. Di.

173
00:14:28.702 --> 00:14:30.636
I'm not here.

174
00:14:30.704 --> 00:14:33.673
Yeah. he's right here.
You wanna speak to him?

175
00:14:33.740 --> 00:14:35.674
No. I don't want to talk to him.

176
00:14:35.742 --> 00:14:37.505
<i>Look. sweetie...</i>

177
00:14:37.577 --> 00:14:39.636
he loves you...

178
00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:41.078
you love him.

179
00:14:41.147 --> 00:14:44.583
You gotta try and work this out.
It's all pretty simple. right?

180
00:14:44.651 --> 00:14:46.744
<i>This is a deal</i>
<i>even I can't screw up.</i>

181
00:14:46.820 --> 00:14:49.254
Tell him he can keep the money.

182
00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:52.924
I don't want any of it.

183
00:15:01.367 --> 00:15:03.028
Davey...

184
00:15:03.103 --> 00:15:05.037
she says she doesn't
want the money.

185
00:15:06.039 --> 00:15:08.030
I don't want the money either.

186
00:15:17.717 --> 00:15:19.708
I'll take it.

187
00:15:19.786 --> 00:15:21.981
I mean.
if nobody else wants it.

188
00:16:01.194 --> 00:16:04.129
<i>The next few weeks without David</i>
<i>felt like months.</i>

189
00:16:05.431 --> 00:16:08.264
<i>I got very good</i>
<i>at staring at walls.</i>

190
00:16:08.334 --> 00:16:09.266
Diana.

191
00:16:12.572 --> 00:16:14.096
The recession has ended.

192
00:16:14.174 --> 00:16:18.270
There's a fella out there wants
to see ten-million-dollar homes.

193
00:16:18.344 --> 00:16:19.606
There is a God.

194
00:16:24.417 --> 00:16:25.850
Find someone else.

195
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:30.046
Find someone else?
Are you nuts?

196
00:16:30.123 --> 00:16:32.114
Do you know what the commission
is on $ 10 million?

197
00:16:32.192 --> 00:16:34.422
- I can't do it.
- You have to do it.

198
00:16:34.494 --> 00:16:36.792
You're the best one I have.

199
00:16:36.863 --> 00:16:40.355
You're the only one I have.
The others are all on caravan.

200
00:16:46.539 --> 00:16:49.872
- I'm sorry. Mr. Langford. I can't.
- Diana.

201
00:16:49.943 --> 00:16:54.004
I would never dream of forcing you
to do anything against your will.

202
00:16:55.248 --> 00:16:57.375
Except this one time.

203
00:16:58.952 --> 00:17:01.546
Now move your ass.
or you're fired.

204
00:17:07.727 --> 00:17:10.662
If you think this is gonna work.
you underestimate me.

205
00:17:36.823 --> 00:17:38.757
You are truly beautiful.

206
00:17:40.827 --> 00:17:42.761
What do you think you're doing?

207
00:17:45.098 --> 00:17:47.032
Looking for a house.

208
00:17:51.504 --> 00:17:54.632
Well. there's Bel-Air. Holmby Hills.
Benedict Canyon. Pacific Palisades.

209
00:17:54.707 --> 00:17:56.572
Where would you like to go first?

210
00:17:56.643 --> 00:17:58.076
Paris.

211
00:17:59.979 --> 00:18:02.413
1120 Bel-Air Road. please.

212
00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:13.724
The ceilings are French gothic.

213
00:18:13.792 --> 00:18:16.192
Renaissance paintings.
as you can see.

214
00:18:16.261 --> 00:18:18.229
Parquet floors throughout.

215
00:18:18.297 --> 00:18:20.231
The bathrooms are Italian marble.

216
00:18:20.899 --> 00:18:22.833
This is the master bath.

217
00:18:27.406 --> 00:18:29.670
Why didn't you return
any of my calls?

218
00:18:30.642 --> 00:18:32.200
Do you like it?

219
00:18:33.812 --> 00:18:35.006
No.

220
00:18:47.359 --> 00:18:49.350
- Thirty million. minimum.
- Do you think?

221
00:18:49.428 --> 00:18:51.487
- I know.
- Well. let's look at it.

222
00:18:51.563 --> 00:18:53.497
It's not for sale.

223
00:18:53.565 --> 00:18:56.033
Everything's for sale.

224
00:19:25.764 --> 00:19:27.698
This is your house. isn't it?

225
00:19:30.435 --> 00:19:32.096
Do you like it?

226
00:19:37.509 --> 00:19:39.875
Well. it's certainly beautiful.

227
00:19:41.713 --> 00:19:43.874
What do you think it needs?

228
00:19:43.949 --> 00:19:46.110
Tell me honestly.

229
00:19:49.054 --> 00:19:50.988
I think it needs a life.

230
00:19:52.524 --> 00:19:55.584
I think it needs furniture...

231
00:19:55.661 --> 00:19:57.925
maybe a couple of dogs
and flowers.

232
00:19:57.996 --> 00:19:59.429
It needs you.

233
00:20:03.235 --> 00:20:05.328
Just forget it.

234
00:20:05.404 --> 00:20:06.701
It just won't work.

235
00:20:06.772 --> 00:20:08.467
Why not?

236
00:20:09.908 --> 00:20:13.241
Because from where we started.
we've got nowhere to go.

237
00:20:13.312 --> 00:20:15.439
You don't know that.

238
00:20:16.782 --> 00:20:18.977
I've never started this way either.

239
00:20:22.354 --> 00:20:23.651
I need you.

240
00:20:28.026 --> 00:20:30.085
No.

241
00:20:30.162 --> 00:20:32.323
You collect things.

242
00:20:35.300 --> 00:20:36.733
Don't you?

243
00:20:38.503 --> 00:20:39.936
Sometimes.

244
00:20:46.178 --> 00:20:47.611
Yeah.

245
00:21:52.678 --> 00:21:55.613
Even if you were extremely rich...

246
00:21:55.681 --> 00:21:57.148
and extremely smart...

247
00:21:57.215 --> 00:21:58.512
can you be president?

248
00:21:59.584 --> 00:22:02.382
You couldn't be president?
Why not?

249
00:22:03.622 --> 00:22:07.023
<i>I took a second job teaching</i>
<i>citizenship just to keep busy.</i>

250
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:12.391
Where were you born?

251
00:22:12.464 --> 00:22:15.399
I was born in Seoul. Korea.

252
00:22:15.467 --> 00:22:16.900
Where was she born?

253
00:22:16.968 --> 00:22:21.132
She was born in Seoul. Korea.

254
00:22:28.380 --> 00:22:30.109
Where were you born. Miguel?

255
00:22:32.784 --> 00:22:33.716
Sorry.

256
00:22:34.619 --> 00:22:35.551
Welcome back.

257
00:22:35.620 --> 00:22:37.781
Where were you born?

258
00:22:37.856 --> 00:22:39.756
Cuba.

259
00:22:39.825 --> 00:22:43.158
So. how do we say "Cuba"
in America?

260
00:22:43.228 --> 00:22:44.160
Cuba.

261
00:22:46.331 --> 00:22:48.492
Hi.

262
00:22:48.567 --> 00:22:51.764
- What are you doing here?
- Isn't this the citizenship class?

263
00:22:51.837 --> 00:22:53.930
- Yes.
- Can I sit in?

264
00:22:55.173 --> 00:22:56.265
It's full.

265
00:22:58.844 --> 00:23:00.402
Okay.

266
00:23:05.851 --> 00:23:06.818
Cuba.

267
00:23:06.885 --> 00:23:08.546
Cuba. Thank you.

268
00:23:24.202 --> 00:23:28.002
Okay. I have a question
for you. Lucy.

269
00:23:28.073 --> 00:23:32.134
Excuse me. Is there something
you'd like to share with us?

270
00:23:32.210 --> 00:23:35.543
I was just saying
that you're an amazing woman.

271
00:23:39.618 --> 00:23:41.552
And...

272
00:23:41.620 --> 00:23:42.678
beautiful.

273
00:23:44.856 --> 00:23:46.289
And talented.

274
00:23:48.126 --> 00:23:49.991
And I am crazy about her.

275
00:23:59.704 --> 00:24:01.797
You're full of surprises.
aren't you?

276
00:24:01.873 --> 00:24:03.636
I'm trying like hell.

277
00:24:04.309 --> 00:24:06.402
I think maybe you should go.

278
00:24:06.478 --> 00:24:08.412
You want me to go?

279
00:24:12.951 --> 00:24:14.976
Nice people.

280
00:24:15.053 --> 00:24:16.486
They want the dream.

281
00:24:17.556 --> 00:24:19.990
They saw it in the flesh tonight.

282
00:24:23.228 --> 00:24:25.162
You have chalk on your face.

283
00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:31.164
I have something
I want to show you.

284
00:24:45.217 --> 00:24:48.243
I didn't know whether you liked
big ones or little ones.

285
00:24:51.156 --> 00:24:54.592
Oh. you're so beautiful.
Come here.

286
00:24:57.128 --> 00:25:00.188
I didn't have much time
to do anything else...

287
00:25:02.967 --> 00:25:04.696
but...

288
00:25:04.769 --> 00:25:06.361
it's a start.

289
00:25:18.983 --> 00:25:20.245
Dance?

290
00:25:23.354 --> 00:25:24.616
I should go.

291
00:25:30.294 --> 00:25:34.458
I remember once when I was young.
I was coming back from someplace.

292
00:25:34.532 --> 00:25:37.467
A movie or something.
I was on the subway.

293
00:25:39.437 --> 00:25:42.702
There was a girl
sitting across from me.

294
00:25:42.774 --> 00:25:45.709
She was wearing this dress
that was buttoned...

295
00:25:46.844 --> 00:25:48.778
clear up right to here.

296
00:25:52.250 --> 00:25:55.185
She was the most beautiful thing
I'd ever seen.

297
00:25:58.056 --> 00:26:00.490
I was shy then.

298
00:26:00.558 --> 00:26:03.721
So when she would look at me...

299
00:26:03.795 --> 00:26:05.729
I would look away.

300
00:26:07.465 --> 00:26:10.457
Then afterwards.
when I would look back...

301
00:26:10.535 --> 00:26:12.799
she would look away.

302
00:26:14.205 --> 00:26:17.197
Then I got to
where I was gonna get off.

303
00:26:17.942 --> 00:26:19.876
Got off. the doors closed...

304
00:26:22.280 --> 00:26:24.544
and as the train
was pulling away...

305
00:26:25.650 --> 00:26:27.948
she looked right at me...

306
00:26:28.019 --> 00:26:30.783
and gave me
the most incredible smile.

307
00:26:33.691 --> 00:26:35.522
It was awful.

308
00:26:36.394 --> 00:26:38.055
I wanted to tear the doors open.

309
00:26:38.129 --> 00:26:40.563
I went back every night.
same time...

310
00:26:41.866 --> 00:26:43.299
for two weeks.

311
00:26:45.903 --> 00:26:47.837
But she never showed up.

312
00:26:50.575 --> 00:26:52.907
That was 30 years ago...

313
00:26:54.112 --> 00:26:56.546
and I don't think
there's a day that goes by...

314
00:26:56.614 --> 00:26:58.548
that I don't think about her.

315
00:27:00.852 --> 00:27:03.286
I don't want that
to happen again.

316
00:27:10.361 --> 00:27:12.090
Just one dance?

317
00:30:46.510 --> 00:30:49.035
I want a word with you. Gage.

318
00:30:49.113 --> 00:30:52.981
See. what you don't know is.
we got a secret. me and Diana.

319
00:30:53.050 --> 00:30:54.574
We're invincible.

320
00:30:55.920 --> 00:30:57.785
Diana. you're so fucking beautiful.

321
00:30:57.855 --> 00:30:59.789
Maybe tomorrow would be better.

322
00:30:59.857 --> 00:31:02.189
Maybe tomorrow
would be a better time?

323
00:31:02.259 --> 00:31:04.193
Hey. I got a suggestion for you.

324
00:31:04.261 --> 00:31:06.559
You know that emblem you got?

325
00:31:07.231 --> 00:31:09.495
The gryphon? The eagle?

326
00:31:09.567 --> 00:31:12.127
I don't think that's a good idea.
I got a better idea.

327
00:31:12.203 --> 00:31:13.761
- Shall I?
- It's all right.

328
00:31:13.838 --> 00:31:15.305
How about the cuckoo?

329
00:31:15.373 --> 00:31:16.806
You know? Because...

330
00:31:16.874 --> 00:31:18.967
I'm talking to you
for a second.

331
00:31:19.043 --> 00:31:22.240
The cuckoo is interesting because
it doesn't have its own nest...

332
00:31:22.313 --> 00:31:26.181
so it moves into other birds' nests
and it destroys their eggs.

333
00:31:26.250 --> 00:31:27.842
David. stop. Just...

334
00:31:31.021 --> 00:31:33.319
You don't love me anymore?

335
00:31:38.429 --> 00:31:41.023
Have I ever told you I love you?

336
00:31:45.736 --> 00:31:47.328
Have a nice dinner.

337
00:31:50.408 --> 00:31:51.841
Help him.

338
00:31:53.544 --> 00:31:55.341
Go inside.

339
00:31:55.413 --> 00:31:56.846
Got him?

340
00:34:28.499 --> 00:34:30.433
You've done a lot since USC.

341
00:34:32.470 --> 00:34:34.370
First in your class...

342
00:34:34.438 --> 00:34:37.965
AIA award. <i>Prix de Rome.</i>

343
00:34:39.076 --> 00:34:40.839
Yeah.

344
00:34:41.612 --> 00:34:43.273
Why would you want this job?

345
00:34:44.515 --> 00:34:47.643
Well. I want to work.

346
00:34:51.155 --> 00:34:53.055
Overqualified.

347
00:34:53.124 --> 00:34:55.058
Fine. Exploit me.

348
00:35:32.129 --> 00:35:35.428
<i>Great architecture is only</i>
<i>gonna come from your passion.</i>

349
00:35:35.499 --> 00:35:37.330
And even that
won't assure you a job.

350
00:35:37.401 --> 00:35:41.235
Louis Kahn died in a mers room
in Penn Station...

351
00:35:41.305 --> 00:35:43.773
and for days
no one claimed the body.

352
00:35:43.841 --> 00:35:46.275
Look at that.
Is that beautiful?

353
00:35:46.344 --> 00:35:48.574
The money men did not weep...

354
00:35:48.646 --> 00:35:51.444
because the great ones
are impossible to deal with.

355
00:35:51.515 --> 00:35:52.880
They're a pain in the ass...

356
00:35:52.950 --> 00:35:56.613
because they know that
if they do their jobs properly...

357
00:35:56.687 --> 00:35:59.178
if they just this once
get it right...

358
00:35:59.256 --> 00:36:02.191
they can actually
lift the human spirit...

359
00:36:02.259 --> 00:36:03.851
take it to a higher place.

360
00:36:09.233 --> 00:36:10.530
What is this?

361
00:36:10.601 --> 00:36:11.795
A brick.

362
00:36:13.270 --> 00:36:15.704
Good. What else?

363
00:36:15.773 --> 00:36:17.741
A weapon.

364
00:36:20.911 --> 00:36:25.314
Louis Kahn said
even a brick wants to be something.

365
00:36:32.189 --> 00:36:36.216
A brick wants to be something.

366
00:36:38.462 --> 00:36:40.430
It aspires.

367
00:36:47.038 --> 00:36:49.336
Even a common. ordinary brick...

368
00:36:49.407 --> 00:36:51.841
wants to be something
more than it is.

369
00:36:57.214 --> 00:37:00.081
It wants to be something
better than it is.

370
00:37:08.893 --> 00:37:11.020
That is what we must be.

371
00:37:14.765 --> 00:37:16.198
See you on Friday.

372
00:37:28.179 --> 00:37:29.874
A brick wants to be something. huh?

373
00:37:29.947 --> 00:37:32.006
I'll bet it doesn't
want to be a lawyer.

374
00:37:32.083 --> 00:37:34.551
- What are you doing here?
- I missed you.

375
00:37:35.219 --> 00:37:36.550
I missed you too.

376
00:37:36.620 --> 00:37:38.053
Thanks.

377
00:37:43.027 --> 00:37:45.655
- How you doir?
- I'm good.

378
00:37:45.729 --> 00:37:47.993
Getting it together.

379
00:37:53.337 --> 00:37:55.396
She wants a divorce.

380
00:37:58.342 --> 00:38:00.333
She wants her freedom and...

381
00:38:02.179 --> 00:38:04.238
if you don't contest it...

382
00:38:04.315 --> 00:38:05.942
you get everything...

383
00:38:06.016 --> 00:38:09.179
the land. the money. everything.

384
00:38:10.488 --> 00:38:11.921
Where is she?

385
00:38:15.126 --> 00:38:16.559
Hi. everybody!

386
00:38:21.065 --> 00:38:22.555
Hi. everybody.
I'm Billy Connolly.

387
00:38:22.633 --> 00:38:24.362
Good-bye. everybody.

388
00:38:24.435 --> 00:38:26.369
You may wonder
what you're doing here...

389
00:38:26.437 --> 00:38:32.069
sitting in the sun as the smell
of the zoo wafts past your nostrils.

390
00:38:32.143 --> 00:38:35.579
The reason you are here
is because you are loaded.

391
00:38:35.646 --> 00:38:39.605
But may I say how brilliant it is
to see so many with an interest...

392
00:38:39.683 --> 00:38:42.049
in the preservation
of endangered species.

393
00:38:42.119 --> 00:38:45.555
Every year we have this unique way
of making money for the cause.

394
00:38:45.623 --> 00:38:47.557
We auction animals.

395
00:38:47.625 --> 00:38:49.616
We bid as high as possible...

396
00:38:49.693 --> 00:38:51.888
and the money goes to sponsor
these lovely beasts.

397
00:38:51.962 --> 00:38:53.896
Let's start with a bang.

398
00:38:53.964 --> 00:38:56.626
We've got a superstar
as a first animal.

399
00:38:56.700 --> 00:38:59.863
Ladies and gentlemen. the hippo.

400
00:38:59.937 --> 00:39:03.874
The animal itself is far too big
and angry to bring along.

401
00:39:04.007 --> 00:39:05.304
Look at this guy.

402
00:39:05.375 --> 00:39:10.608
Thousands and thousands of pounds
of aggressive. hostile cellulite.

403
00:39:10.680 --> 00:39:14.047
Weighs slightly less
than the average school bus.

404
00:39:14.117 --> 00:39:16.483
Look at that magnificent beastie.

405
00:39:16.553 --> 00:39:20.546
To put him in a better light. to
relieve you of some serious money...

406
00:39:21.658 --> 00:39:23.956
Thank you very much.

407
00:39:24.027 --> 00:39:26.495
We have a kissy-kissy picture.

408
00:39:27.597 --> 00:39:29.030
Isn't that nice?

409
00:39:32.335 --> 00:39:35.270
Ladies and gentlemen. I couldn't
even dream of starting the bid...

410
00:39:35.338 --> 00:39:36.896
below $ 10.000.

411
00:39:36.973 --> 00:39:39.942
- Now. I know it's a lot of money...
- Thirty.

412
00:39:40.010 --> 00:39:43.810
Thirty thousand dollars.
ladies and gentlemen!

413
00:39:45.015 --> 00:39:47.711
Call me a sentimental old fool.

414
00:39:47.784 --> 00:39:49.649
Do I hear 35?

415
00:39:49.719 --> 00:39:52.654
- Thirty-five.
- Thirty-five thousand dollars!

416
00:39:52.722 --> 00:39:55.316
- Forty.
- Forty thousand dollars!

417
00:39:55.392 --> 00:39:57.690
- Forty-five thousand.
- Forty-five thousand!

418
00:39:57.761 --> 00:40:01.162
- Fifty.
- Fifty thousand dollars!

419
00:40:02.165 --> 00:40:04.690
I can't believe it.
That's extraordinary.

420
00:40:04.768 --> 00:40:06.531
Fifty thousand once.

421
00:40:06.603 --> 00:40:09.163
Fifty thousand twice.
ladies and gentlemen.

422
00:40:09.940 --> 00:40:11.669
One million dollars.

423
00:40:15.378 --> 00:40:17.369
- Wow.
- Who is he?

424
00:40:18.615 --> 00:40:20.105
I'm sorry?

425
00:40:20.183 --> 00:40:22.481
One million dollars.

426
00:40:24.955 --> 00:40:27.719
Did you say
one million dollars. sir?

427
00:40:28.491 --> 00:40:29.549
Yeah.

428
00:40:29.626 --> 00:40:33.153
Ladies and gentlemen.
one million dollars!

429
00:40:33.229 --> 00:40:37.256
Goodness! Would anybody care to
top that. ladies and gentlemen?

430
00:40:38.335 --> 00:40:39.700
I didn't think so.

431
00:40:39.769 --> 00:40:43.227
In that case. sir. I believe
you're the proud owner of a hippo.

432
00:40:43.306 --> 00:40:44.898
Congratulations.

433
00:40:58.755 --> 00:41:00.017
Hello. Diana.

434
00:41:00.090 --> 00:41:03.457
Ladies and gentlemen.
the next animal is an ostrich.

435
00:41:03.526 --> 00:41:05.756
I really wanted you
to have that money.

436
00:41:05.829 --> 00:41:08.354
And I really wanted you
to have that hippo.

437
00:41:12.268 --> 00:41:14.702
Maybe you two
would like a moment alone.

438
00:41:19.976 --> 00:41:23.571
So can we hear a bid
of. maybe. a million?

439
00:41:23.646 --> 00:41:27.548
That was a joke.
Start at 30.000. Do I hear 40?

440
00:41:29.252 --> 00:41:31.049
So.

441
00:41:33.656 --> 00:41:35.521
- How are you...
- I hear you're teaching.

442
00:41:35.592 --> 00:41:37.685
- Go ahead.
- I'm sorry.

443
00:41:38.828 --> 00:41:40.762
Yeah. I'm teaching.

444
00:41:43.566 --> 00:41:47.366
It doesn't pay much. but at least
I get to talk about architecture.

445
00:41:48.471 --> 00:41:51.133
You know how I love
to talk about architecture.

446
00:41:51.207 --> 00:41:54.142
Oh. my goodness.
Don't leave. ladies and gentlemen.

447
00:41:54.210 --> 00:41:57.145
It's just a little shower.
Please!

448
00:41:57.213 --> 00:42:00.546
A checkbook
makes an ideal umbrella.

449
00:42:00.617 --> 00:42:03.814
Do we have a dolphin?
Have we a dolphin or an octopus?

450
00:42:03.887 --> 00:42:06.219
How about tropical fish?

451
00:42:06.289 --> 00:42:09.122
I know! You're running home
for more cash. I get it.

452
00:42:09.192 --> 00:42:12.787
Come on. ladies and gentlemen.
You can find the money.

453
00:42:12.862 --> 00:42:15.422
Oh. to hell. I'm gone.

454
00:42:24.474 --> 00:42:26.669
I have to talk to you
about what happened.

455
00:42:26.743 --> 00:42:30.042
- Don't. Don't.
- No. no. no. I have to.

456
00:42:30.113 --> 00:42:31.774
Just hear me out.

457
00:42:35.018 --> 00:42:38.249
I think the mistake
I made in Vegas...

458
00:42:38.321 --> 00:42:41.518
was thinking that I could
forget what we did.

459
00:42:43.760 --> 00:42:46.991
I thought we were invincible.

460
00:42:47.997 --> 00:42:51.626
But now I know that the things
people in love do to each other...

461
00:42:51.701 --> 00:42:53.999
they remember.

462
00:42:54.070 --> 00:42:57.528
If they stay together.
it's not because they forget.

463
00:42:57.607 --> 00:42:59.598
It's because they forgive.

464
00:43:06.416 --> 00:43:07.849
I was just...

465
00:43:11.421 --> 00:43:14.356
I was just so afraid
that you wanted him.

466
00:43:15.825 --> 00:43:19.124
No. actually I was afraid
that you were right to want him.

467
00:43:24.234 --> 00:43:26.828
'Cause I thought
he was the better man.

468
00:43:32.775 --> 00:43:35.209
And I know now he's not.

469
00:43:36.479 --> 00:43:38.140
He's just got more money.

470
00:45:10.707 --> 00:45:12.641
I think we should talk.

471
00:45:13.476 --> 00:45:15.410
I am very happy.

472
00:45:16.846 --> 00:45:17.938
Shackleford.

473
00:45:19.249 --> 00:45:21.979
Did you ever see me like this?

474
00:45:22.051 --> 00:45:24.451
Can't say that I have.

475
00:45:24.520 --> 00:45:26.954
Diana is the reason.

476
00:45:27.023 --> 00:45:28.615
Enough for any man.

477
00:45:28.691 --> 00:45:30.750
She is the best of them.

478
00:45:30.827 --> 00:45:32.260
Absolutely.

479
00:45:33.863 --> 00:45:35.797
You are the best of them.

480
00:45:37.033 --> 00:45:38.398
The best of them?

481
00:45:39.469 --> 00:45:41.937
You said I'm the best of them?

482
00:45:42.005 --> 00:45:44.098
You are.

483
00:45:46.676 --> 00:45:48.473
I don't understand.

484
00:45:49.979 --> 00:45:53.142
Shackleford.
could you explain it to her?

485
00:45:53.216 --> 00:45:54.649
What?

486
00:45:55.918 --> 00:45:57.783
I could do that. sir...

487
00:45:58.955 --> 00:46:02.618
but somehow I feel Ms. Murphy would
rather hear it directly from you.

488
00:46:02.692 --> 00:46:05.388
Okay. All right.

489
00:46:05.461 --> 00:46:08.157
She's the best
of the million-dollar club.

490
00:46:08.197 --> 00:46:09.432
Obviously.

491
00:46:12.668 --> 00:46:15.603
- The million-dollar club?
- Now you've got it.

492
00:46:17.907 --> 00:46:19.841
You told me
you'd never done that before.

493
00:46:19.909 --> 00:46:22.503
How many members
would you say there are?

494
00:46:23.279 --> 00:46:25.213
- Members?
- Yeah.

495
00:46:26.916 --> 00:46:28.543
Worldwide?

496
00:46:28.617 --> 00:46:30.050
Yeah.

497
00:46:31.320 --> 00:46:32.912
A couple dozen.

498
00:46:34.356 --> 00:46:37.052
Remember the one
that wouldn't stop hiccuping?

499
00:46:37.126 --> 00:46:38.423
What?

500
00:46:38.494 --> 00:46:40.189
The waitress from Oklahoma.

501
00:46:40.262 --> 00:46:43.823
Every time you came near her
she would convulse into hiccups.

502
00:46:45.901 --> 00:46:48.369
Yeah. I had forgotten.

503
00:46:48.437 --> 00:46:49.870
Quite a night.

504
00:46:51.640 --> 00:46:53.369
The best thing of it is...

505
00:46:53.442 --> 00:46:56.434
you know
if you're sexually compatible...

506
00:46:57.513 --> 00:46:59.845
right from the start.

507
00:47:10.259 --> 00:47:12.921
Shackleford.
would you stop the car?

508
00:47:42.525 --> 00:47:44.493
Thank you. John.

509
00:47:48.430 --> 00:47:49.795
Good-bye.

510
00:47:50.900 --> 00:47:52.333
Good-bye.

511
00:47:54.637 --> 00:47:56.104
Oh.

512
00:47:59.508 --> 00:48:01.408
Here.

513
00:48:05.281 --> 00:48:06.771
For luck.

514
00:48:10.185 --> 00:48:11.447
Yeah.

515
00:48:15.391 --> 00:48:17.450
- Take care of him.
- Sure.

516
00:48:26.201 --> 00:48:27.793
What was all that about?

517
00:48:30.506 --> 00:48:32.440
I wanted to end it.

518
00:48:36.812 --> 00:48:40.612
She never would have looked at me
the way she did at him.

519
00:49:31.634 --> 00:49:35.570
<i>Seven years ago David proposed to me</i>
<i>on the pier at Paradise Cove.</i>

